subSubSection.paragraph:
Cephalothorax: carapace (
Figure 42
) 1.13–1.28 times longer than broad; sub-rectangular; without any traces of eyes; epistome small; with 22 setae arranged 4: 4: 4: 4: 6; without furrows; with three pairs of small lyrifissures, first and second pairs placed near anterior margin, and third pair placed near edge of posterior row. Manducatory process with one long distal and one long sub-distal seta, without sub-oral seta; remainder of maxilla with seven setae (
Figure 45
). Chaetotaxy of coxae I–IV: 4–5: 4: 4: 6. Posterior section of coxae II slightly overlapping anterior section of coxae III (
Figure 45
).
